People take photos as a semi-submersible drilling platform leaves its "birthplace" in Yantai, East China's Shandong Province on Wednesday. It's headed for work in the rough, cold waters of Norway. The platform, built by a plant of CIMC Raffles, is designed to function at temperatures as low as -20 C. Photo: VCG
  
